<p>Ever have trouble connecting your Mac to another WiFi network even when Windows machines easily connect? Ever try to share files with a Windows machine but run into trouble there? How about if you&rsquo;re a Gmail user but can&rsquo;t figure out quite the right way to manage your Mail archives without dealing with the duplicate messages caused by the &ldquo;All Mail&rdquo; mailbox? Well, you&rsquo;re in luck. Download, press play, and enjoy, because John F. Braun and Dave Hamilton are here to answer these questions &mdash; and quite a few more! &mdash; on today&rsquo;s episode of Mac Geek Gab! You can even send in your own questions to be answered in a future show, too!</p>
